---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PhilosophyCallout from '../../components/docs/PhilosophyCallout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Quiet Authority" description="Cleo's design philosophy">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Quiet Authority</h1>
    <hr class="section-accent-rule" />

    <p class="page-lead">
      Confidence that does not shout. Warmth that does not perform. A product that steps back as
      work completes.
    </p>

    <h2>What it means</h2>
    <p>
      Quiet Authority is Cleo's design philosophy: the visual and interaction language of someone
      who knows exactly what they are doing and does not need to prove it. The interface carries
      competence through restraint — cool palette, humanist typography at scale, single warm accent,
      slow motion, plain language.
    </p>

    <h2>What it is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Not startup energy — no bright blues, no bold weights, no celebration animations</li>
      <li>Not clinical coldness — warmth lives in cream text on slate, in serif headlines, in copy that names the wound first</li>
      <li>Not minimalism for its own sake — every element earns its place in the therapist's emotional journey</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The test</h2>
    <p>
      Before shipping any surface, ask: does this make a burned-out, skeptical physical therapist
      feel understood before they feel sold to? If not, remove or rewrite until it does.
    </p>

    <PhilosophyCallout title="This documentation site">
      <p>
        This site is built in Quiet Authority. It is not describing the philosophy from the outside
        — it is demonstrating it. If the docs feel calm, editorial, and considered, the system is
        working.
      </p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
